The paper deals with algorithms for processing digital elevation models, which are commonly used in computer graphics, geographic information systems, and numerical analysis. The paper's focus on filling depressions and labeling watersheds suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) and computational topology (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of priority queues and time complexity analysis suggests that it also belongs to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The mention of flow directions and safety checks suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
